National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan and National Security Advisor Sydney Mufamadi of South Africa had a phone conversation. They discussed President Ramaphosa's response to concerns about the activities of Lady R last year. They reaffirmed the strong partnership between South Africa and the United States and their commitment to shared priorities such as trade, investment, infrastructure, health, and climate. They also discussed the situation in Ukraine and pledged to work towards a just and lasting peace. Sullivan thanked South Africa for hosting the African Growth and Opportunity Act (AGOA) Forum and expressed condolences for the passing of Aziz Pahad, a South African politician and anti-apartheid activist.